![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/75d489c5-5039-4589-9f1e-b43243ce2fbc/ee350.jpg?format=original)

In this episode, we take a deep dive into _The Boy Wonder_ by Juni Ba, featuring none other than Damian Wayne as the book’s protagonist. We explore how Ba reimagines the legacy of Batman’s son, adding fresh layers to Damian’s character through vibrant art and dynamic storytelling. Join us as we break down his journey, the emotional depth of his challenges, and how Ba’s unique style brings new life to the familiar world of Gotham. Whether you're a die-hard Damian Wayne fan or new to his story, this episode is packed with insights you won’t want to miss!  
  
Please leave us a **_review_** on [**ITunes**](https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/major-issues-podcast/id1321720972) so we can grow our audience and grow as podcasters! Rate us wherever podcasts are found. Don't forget to check out our merchandise! All episodes of Major Issues are brought to you by **ComicBook Clique**, the only stop for the latest and greatest things to come to comic books and comic book media.

